1581 <div>

1582 <h2>

1583 <strong>Browse Our</strong>

1584 <strong>2021</strong>&nbsp;

1585 <strong>Collection of Cabinet Hardware</strong>&nbsp;

1586 </h2>

1587 <p>Our collection features styles available in multiple finishes such as brass, polished nickel, oil-rubbed bronze, and more. Whether youre looking for a rustic look, transitional, or contemporary, we have the perfect pulls and knobs for your cabinetry. Browse the collection now or read tips on

1588 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-choose-cabinet-hardware/" target="_blank">how to choose cabinet hardware</a>.&nbsp;

1589 </p>

1590 <h3>Cabinet Hardware</h3>

1591 <p>

1592 <em>

1593 <strong>Cabinet hardware</strong>

1594 </em> is classified into two main types: pulls and knobs. Use one type or both, each have certain qualities and styles that make them useful and beautiful.&nbsp;

1595 </p>

1596 <ul>

1597 <li>

1598 <em>

1599 <strong>Cabinet pulls</strong>

1600 </em> also referred to as handles, typically longer than a knob. These are available in multiple designs including bar, cup, arch, handle, and others.

1601 <br> &nbsp;

1602 </li>

1603 <li>

1604 <em>

1605 <strong>Cabinet knobs</strong>

1606 </em> are typically smaller than a pull, coming in styles like birdcage, round, oval, square, rectangle, and other shapes to match your cabinets.&nbsp;

1607 </li>

1608 </ul>

1609 <p>Both styles are available multiple finishes such as chrome, brushed nickel, brass, black, stainless steel, and more. To find matching sets, we recommend shopping by collection or by finish as your browse. If you have questions or would like an opinion on hardware for your cabinets,

1610 <a href="mailto:design@vevano.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">

1611 <u>contact</u>

1612 </a> our design experts. &nbsp;

1613 </p>
